1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:05,500
Architecture Governance Copilot is our Accelerate 3.0
proof of concept from Two Tokens One Brain.

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:10,700
It turns architecture work into an accountable,
AI-assisted governance record.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:16,000
Product Owners and development teams prepare
the Solution Intent in Confluence.

4
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:21,000
An Azure DevOps governance ticket tracks the review.

5
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:25,500
A Domain Architect reviews through Teams meetings
and revision rounds.

6
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,700
This proof of concept uses synthetic local content
representing those sources.

7
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:33,800
Those handoffs scatter decisions, risks,
actions, and evidence.

8
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:37,700
Teams then rebuild the governance record manually.

9
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:43,000
AI synthesizes confirmed project context
into a draft Solution Intent.

10
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:48,000
It interprets the SI and transcript into structured,
evidence-linked governance proposals.

11
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,700
Humans retain control.

12
00:00:52,191 --> 00:00:56,783
The target front end runs in Service Bench;
backend API and governed state run in SKE.

13
00:00:56,878 --> 00:01:02,043
Permission-aware Confluence, Teams, and Azure DevOps connectors
retrieve only sources selected by the user.

14
00:01:02,139 --> 00:01:06,635
Azure Repos supplies the chosen repository and branch;
Azure Boards supplies governance metadata.

15
00:01:06,730 --> 00:01:13,704
The backend builds a context package for human confirmation;
only that approved scope reaches AI Factory, or AIF.

16
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:19,000
The application opens at Project Context,
the first of five visible stages.

17
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:24,000
The fictional workspace shows its ADO reference,
SI template, and repository branch.

18
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:29,000
It also shows supporting documents
and source-selection controls.

19
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:34,000
In production, permission-aware connectors retrieve
only user-confirmed sources.

20
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:39,000
Here, deterministic synthetic fixtures keep
the demonstration reliable and offline.

21
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:43,800
I inspect each preview, refresh the context,
and explicitly confirm the package.

22
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Generate SI Draft validates confirmed context
before AI-assisted drafting.

23
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:54,000
It creates an editable proposal,
with source details available beneath it.

24
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:59,000
This is a drafting aid,
not publication or approval.

25
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:04,000
I confirm the draft before continuing.

26
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:09,000
The confirmed SI is preserved with the matching
Teams-style transcript and review metadata.

27
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:14,000
Analyze Review starts AI-assisted analysis
of the review evidence.

28
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:19,000
A separate Human Review page opens
with a Changes Requested outcome.

29
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:24,000
The summary covers decisions, findings, risk, actions,
an open question, and missing information.

30
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:29,000
The decision accepts managed PostgreSQL
as the system of record.

31
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:34,000
The proposals identify unresolved failover,
resilience, and support-ownership evidence.

32
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:39,000
They also identify a capacity risk.

33
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:44,000
Every proposal retains a source quote from
the Solution Intent, transcript, or both.

34
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:49,000
The reviewer can inspect evidence, edit fields,
and include or exclude items.

35
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:54,000
I change the first action owner
to the synthetic value Taylor Kim.

36
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:59,000
Then I exclude the unresolved Redis question.
Evidence stays read-only.

37
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:04,000
That human checkpoint is essential: AI proposes
structure and evidence links.

38
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:09,000
It does not decide the outcome,
approve architecture, or publish records.

39
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:14,000
The Domain Architect and project team
retain accountability.

40
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:19,000
Only after human review do I confirm the record
and generate outputs.

41
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:24,000
The completed package preserves those choices in the
review record and Azure DevOps work-item previews.

42
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:29,700
Nothing was submitted to Azure DevOps.

43
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:36,000
AI reduces first-pass drafting
and review administration.

44
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:42,000
Evidence grounding makes every proposal
easier to verify.

45
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:47,640
Every record remains human-reviewed, and authority
stays with the Domain Architect.

46
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:53,000
Architecture Governance Copilot creates a
human-controlled path from governed context,

47
00:03:53,083 --> 00:03:57,750
through AI assistance, to accountable action.
Two Tokens One Brain.
